author: {'steamid': '76561199520321705', 'num_games_owned': 20, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 948, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 139, 'playtime_at_review': 887, 'last_played': 1712458742}
review:
Clone Drone In The Danger Zone To Put Clearly Is Not For Everyone, with Its Blocky Yet Appealing Graphics, And Difficult Controls It Wont Be The Right Fir For Everyone.
Combat
While Its Combat can Feel Klunky at Times Every Time You Die It Almost Always feels Like Your Fault, There Was Something You Could Have Done Better To Not Die Where You Did. 
  The Sword Is The Basic All rounder Its Most Powerful Ability Is Its Ability To Block And Reflect Arrows, Allowing You To Easily Kill Off Archers. 
  The Bow Is A Great Utility Item As It Acts As A Boss Killer Being Able To Take Out Big Bots That Just Eat The Arrows, Although It has the Weakness As Described As The Sword Beats It Solidly.
  The hammer Is Basically the "Ive Had Enough of This" As It Steamrolls Bots that get Too Close, While Its Not Nearly As Defense As The Sword It has More Range That The Sword Does And It Does great At Taking Down Targets, its Main Downside Is That Its Slower That The Other Wears.
  The Spear Is The Counter To Armor As Instead Of A Typical Swinging Motion That the Sword And Hammer Has It Goes Directly Forwards, While Arrows can Achieve The Same Effect You Need To be Precise And Cant Have Upgraded Arrow Width. Along With This You Also get A Shield That Takes Arrows And Stops Them In Their Tracks.
  Specials
 Flame Breath - Is Great For Survival Not So Much Killing, While Most Other Weapons End Up Killing You If You lose your Right Hand/Arm With Flame Breath You can Still Attack And Walk Around Without A Weapon. Along With This It may Just be A Surprise To Those Who have To Deal With Annoying Robots
 Kicking - While It Doesnt Kill it Deals With Bots that you Cant Kill By Knocking Them to The Ground Letting You Kill Them Easier. Buying This Upgrade Also Lets You Get Life Alert Which is helpful For When You get Knocked on Your Ass.
  Unlockables
 Upon beat Specific Challenges Ranging From "Only Use This Weapon" To The "You Cannot Choose Your Own upgrades" These Often Will Either Unlock A Fire Version of A Weapon That can Deal More Damage And Deals Damage Over Time Or A Trophy That Can be Displayed In The Upgrade Room.
 Story
While The Story is Interesting I Often Find Myself More Invested In The old Person I Am Actually Playing As rather than Whats Happening Around Me, The Story Acts More As A Supliment To The Game Play. Meant To be More Of A Background To Explain What is Happening Rather Than Being At Its Forefront.

author: {'steamid': '76561198354852992', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 14527, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 4, 'playtime_at_review': 14527, 'last_played': 1711840654}
review:
Behold, Clone Drone in the Danger Zone, the epitome of gaming excellence! In a realm where mediocrity reigns, this masterpiece stands tall as a beacon of innovation and excitement. From its inception, it has captivated players with its ingenious concept and flawless execution, setting a new standard for gaming greatness.

Step into the Danger Zone, where every moment is a heart-pounding adventure. With intuitive controls and seamless gameplay, you'll find yourself immersed in a world of robotic gladiatorial combat like never before. Each slice of your sword, each dodge of a deadly trap, is a testament to the sheer brilliance of this game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198119801640', 'num_games_owned': 28, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 1961, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 58, 'playtime_at_review': 1903, 'last_played': 1712272010}
review:
Are you ready to immerse yourself in a whirlwind of robot-slicing action and adrenaline-pumping challenges? Look no further than "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone"! This indie gem is a masterclass in addictive gameplay, combining intuitive controls, strategic combat, and endless replayability into one thrilling package.

From the moment you step into the arena, you're thrust into a world where survival is the name of the game. As a human consciousness transferred into a robot gladiator, your task is simple yet exhilarating: outmaneuver, outsmart, and outfight your robotic adversaries to become the last one standing. And with each victory, you're rewarded with upgrades that empower you to face even deadlier foes.

What truly sets "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone" apart is its seamless blend of skill-based combat and roguelike elements. Every decision matters, whether it's choosing between different weapon loadouts, utilizing environmental hazards to your advantage, or mastering intricate combat maneuvers. And with its procedurally generated levels, no two playthroughs are ever the same, keeping you on the edge of your seat with each new challenge.

But it's not just the gameplay that shines in this title. "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone" boasts charming voxel graphics that perfectly complement its quirky and humorous tone. Whether you're slicing through enemies with a laser sword or dodging deadly traps, every moment is brought to life with vibrant visuals and satisfying sound effects, creating an immersive experience that's impossible to put down.

And let's not forget the community-driven aspect of the game. With a dedicated fanbase and robust modding support, the fun never ends in the Danger Zone. From user-created levels to custom challenges, there's always something new to discover and conquer, ensuring that you'll be coming back for more long after you've mastered the core game.

In conclusion, "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone" is a shining example of indie game excellence. With its addictive gameplay, charming aesthetics, and endless replay value, it's a must-play for anyone craving a thrilling and unforgettable gaming experience. So grab your sword, steel your nerves, and dive headfirst into the Danger Zone ‚Äì adventure awaits!

author: {'steamid': '76561198967167115', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 2072, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 1, 'playtime_at_review': 2072, 'last_played': 1711845444}
review: I love this game. The levels are fun and creative, and the community is involved. There is multi-player and single-player options available. My only complaint is that the game gets very repetitive. Once you complete the story mode and do all the challenges, all you have left is endless mode and a battle royal type game-mode. This may be a deal breaker for some people, but if you enjoy a good story and interesting game elements, this game is for you. If you value replay-ability, this may not be your favorites. Overall, a great game, would recommend to the average gamer. 9/10

author: {'steamid': '76561199398319624', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 938, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 202, 'playtime_at_review': 735, 'last_played': 1712249622}
review:
Lo jugue mucho solo, ahora pude jugarlo online. Tengo muchas cosas para decir, algunas buenas otras muy buenas y otras muy malas:

1- El juego es muy vicioso. Era el mejor juego de este tipo que he jugado hasta que a los creadores se les ocurri√≥ aumentar la dificultad del mismo empeorandolo levemente por los siqguientes motivos: Antes del arreglo, cuando le pegabas con la espada al enemigo primero y a la espada despues, matabas al enemigo. Ahora si le pegas primero al enemigo y luego a la espada, el enemigo cubre el golpe, cosa que en la realidad no pasar√≠a (ya s√© que es un juego de todos modos!).

2- Otro error drastico que aumento la dificultad mucho es lo siguiente: antiguamente si le pegabas al enemigo en una region del cuerpo sin armadura, le hacias da√±o. Ahora pareceria como que primero tienen que caer todas las partes de sus armaduras para luego comenzar a hacerle da√±o al cuerpo. Esto es muy malo, sobre todo para aquellos acostumbrados a jugar cuando el juego recien sali√≥. Ah√≠ si con la espada sola pod√≠as inspirarte en obi wan kenobi. Ahora para pelear contra los swordman 4 con armadura si o si tenes que tener espada de fuego 2 o flamebreath, de lo contrario no le haces ni cosquillas y te cortan como si fueras manteca. 

3- Por lo demas el juego esta bien. Logre pasar los 5 capitulos en insane y ademas llegue en modo sin fin al 77 o 78 y me di cuenta que los niveles empiezan a repetirse. Tengo el video de los niveles 70 al 78, si quieren puedo pasarselos al que desee ver como jugarlos. 

Para terminar una pregunta: Alguno avanzo mas de estos niveles? que me dicen?

review: Very fun game! The story is surprisingly interesting even though it is quite short. The endless mode can provide you with a ton of fun, and you can try out all of the different abilities and weapon combos to decimate your enemies. You can even play with your friends! The combat is the most important part of the game and Doborog games nailed it. You can destroy your enemies while fighting them(cutting off limbs burning them etc). It's hard to explain how fun this game is, but I would definitely recommend at least trying the demo. Enjoy!

author: {'steamid': '76561198866556471', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 26, 'playtime_forever': 4001, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 83, 'playtime_at_review': 3918, 'last_played': 1711592752}
review:
Clone Drone in the Danger Zone catapults players into an exhilarating and unique experience that seamlessly blends fast-paced combat, humor, and creative mechanics. The game's premise of battling through waves of robots in deadly arenas is not only entertaining but executed with a level of polish that captivates players from the get-go.

The combat mechanics are a shining beacon of the game's excellence. The swordplay feels fluid, and the ability to slice and dice through enemies with precision is immensely satisfying. The inclusion of various weapons, upgrades, and abilities ensures that each playthrough is a dynamic and strategic endeavor, making the combat both accessible and deep.

The game's sense of humor is a delightful touch. The witty commentary and quirky interactions contribute to a lighthearted atmosphere, making the intense battles feel even more enjoyable. The developers' creativity shines through in both the design of the enemies and the humorous dialogue, creating a gaming experience that is as amusing as it is engaging.

Clone Drone's innovation extends to its Twitch integration, allowing streamers and their audiences to directly influence the gameplay. This interaction not only enhances the entertainment value but also fosters a sense of community involvement that is rare in the gaming world.

However, the glaring downside to Clone Drone in the Danger Zone lies in its server issues. The occasional lag spikes and connectivity problems can disrupt the otherwise seamless experience, leading to frustrating moments during critical gameplay. This issue, while not pervasive, does detract from the overall enjoyment, especially in the more intense stages where split-second decisions are crucial.

Despite the server-related drawbacks, Clone Drone in the Danger Zone remains a stellar title that excels in its genre. The combination of engaging combat, humorous elements, and innovative features makes it a standout experience. With a bit of improvement on the server stability front, this game could easily reach even greater heights and solidify its place as a beloved indie gem.

review:
Whatever you do: at least try the demo! I already had lots of fun with that, not just with the deceptively simple yet rewarding combat but also the hilarious arena commentator bots. And once I bought the game, I was actually surprised that the campaign is genuinely entertaining, with lots of humour, and some great gameplay twists. The endless and challenge modes, which are similar to but expand upon the gameplay in the demo with some interesting mechanics, offering enough replayability (in addition to the Workshop content and free updates).

So go ahead and play the demo, then buy the game!

author: {'steamid': '76561198050855946', 'num_games_owned': 122, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 379660, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 89, 'playtime_at_review': 368884, 'last_played': 1712184089}
review: As you can see, I have played this game for just "a few" hours :) I am mentally sane (totally) and I abseloutely (don't) have a life. Now to get to the actual review. I've been playing this game since 2018, and have liked it ever since. The Mechanics are great, level design is awesome, and the story is well told. The only dislikes I have about the game is the co-op mode. I don't like co-op for some reason, it feels bland and literally all randoms suck ass. Most of the time the other guy dies and I have to do it alone. And it's extreamly easy to hack in co-op. I feel like the anti-cheat isn't as functional as in LBS there. It's possebile to make yourself invincibile to the enemies by making their weapons disappear using a simple mod. This is why damage should NOT be calculated on the clients side. Cause then stuff like that is possebile. You should also make more level editor tutorials, I feel like that most of the important mechanics in the level editor are not clearly explained. Some of them aren't even mentioned at all in the tutorials. It is too beginner friendly, make tutorials for advanced level editors, that already know the basics of the editor. Anyways, this is my review for the game. Hope this helps anyone! Also I don't know what all those people are on about that it's "overpriced".  This game is definetily worth $20 (not being sarcastic) I bought this game like a while ago, and barely had any issues with it. Also please add more garbage bots for LBS. I rarely played LBS after I got to 1000 wins cause there's not really a reason to play it anymore. - Trax

author: {'steamid': '76561198091076720', 'num_games_owned': 126, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 347, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 211, 'last_played': 1705967789}
review:
The game's fun on its own, but the multiplayer aspect is very disappointing.

Is has no steamworks support nor P2P support. 
All servers are hosted publicly, no dedicated servers and for private games you have to join using a code so no inviting and joining directly through steam.
Private games are really fun but public games take a very long time to start since after every round you have to effectively rejoin the server, which depending on your region may have latency issues as well.

For endless mode, difficulty doesn't seem to increase past a certain point. After we had all upgrades unlocked it was a slog to keep going since it was a constant repeat of the same maps, the same enemies.

For Last Bot Standing, private servers have a glaring lack of customization. You have a set amount of credits (4) you can spend and that's it, you can't increase/decrease initial credits nor can you lock certain upgrades, which would otherwise allow for some very interesting matches.

Otherwise, a really fun game to play with friends, but I wouldn't recommend it unless it's on sale. May amend my review if they ever add steamworks support since that's my biggest qualm with the game.

author: {'steamid': '76561199124621514', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 10075, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 8809, 'last_played': 1708380621}
review: I had a BLAST when I played this game. I played many hours of this game, have every achievement, and is waiting for the human plush to come back in the shop. This game never gets old. I'm a person that is not a fan of skill trees but some how they pulled it off. The fact That there is a sword, spear, bow, and hammer is CRAZY! Also, with the other things like kick and jet pack that are so cool! I like how instead of having to buy arrows and foul, this game has its own thing, energy so it makes the game way more fun. And it is cool to hear the commentators talk about the next level so you know what to upgrade.  Not only that, the fighting is really fun! Having the different types of robots all trying to make you garbage is amazing! This game could just have an endless mode and it would be amazing, but they took it to the next level! Having a story line, having endless like I said, Having challenges, having a twitch mode for streaming, multiplayer that you can play with you friends, but if you don't have any, you can play multiplayer endless, multiplayer challenges, a game mode that's called "last bot standing" and its one of the best game modes ever! You can even make or play levels form other people. And there is achievements that are really fun and give you rewards  like fire hammer, mega kick, flame breath, and much more! I will be honest that there is some rage inducing ones like random upgrade challenge, armor only challenge, insane chapter five, one, and two. I had no problem with them but many "normal" people would HATE them.  They even have there own store with mugs and shirts and pushiest. Over all, Clone Drone in the Danger Zone should have WAY more player base and should be the game of the year forever. Thank you Doborog for making this dream of a game come to life. Can't wait for the next update!

author: {'steamid': '76561199221942081', 'num_games_owned': 56, 'num_reviews': 26, 'playtime_forever': 1842, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1842, 'last_played': 1705166795}
review:
Clone Drone is super weird and unique game that I spent more time on than I expected to. Don't let the visuals fool you though, this is a very difficult game.

Visually this game looks very simple. Everything is made of blocks. All the enemies in this game have different designs and different colours to make them easy to tell apart and to tell how dangerous they are. Music is also pretty good. All characters in this game that can speak have the generic robot voices that you would assume they might have.

The gameplay is what you're really here for. The gameplay focuses almost entirely on the combat and the combat is quite unique compared to other games. There are no health bars in this game. You die whenever your body takes too much damage. These can evolve losing both your legs, losing your right arm, because then you can't hold weapons, your torso taking too much damage, or your head taking too much damage. Your strikes are directional, you can either strike left, right , or straight down. Your weapon will cut wherever it lands in that direction, so its possible to cut enemies in halve, or cut off their arm, or their leg. This game also has a lot of content. There's the single player endless mode and a co-op endless mode, there are single player challenges and co-op challenges, there's a free for all pvp mode, private duels, twitch mode for streamers, and a campaign. The first two chapters of the campaign is pretty simple, it's chapter three where the campaign gets insane, it's a lot of fun. There's also a workshop for this game, so there is always more content if need it. A warning though for this game is that it's quite difficult. Some flaws with this game is that the co-op challenges drag on for way too long and the UI sometimes glitches and needs to be reloaded.

The game does have a story, but it's very simple and only serves as a set up for the game and is there for the purpose of the campaign mode. The humour will work for some people,but will annoy others. Personally I think its fine.

In conclusion, you can get a good amount of hours out of this game and the pvp mode is pretty competitive. Combat is unique and different. I would say though to buy this on sale just to be safe.

review: This game has a cool premise, but fails to be fun to play. The combat is slow, in my 43 minutes I used all the weapons the game had to offer. And none of them except the sword was tolerable. developer_response:
Totally fair, I know the game isn't for everyone. Appreciate ya trying it out though, and if ya want, feel free to get a refund on Clone Drone! We always folks to get something that they're gonna really like for their $$, so if that's a different game for ya, we totally support that

Clone Drone in the Danger Zone. An instant classic. One of those video games that reminds you why video games are so much fun, and why you enjoy playing them.

author: {'steamid': '76561199087442846', 'num_games_owned': 27, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 1364, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1199, 'last_played': 1703189825}
review:
Nice and chill offline game. A blast with friends as an online game too, but absolutely not worth $20 dollars. This is a $10 below game, and I would recommend this game in general but the price is egregious.

If you're intrigued regardless of the high price, Clone Drone is one of those challenge games where you want to unlock all the achievements even if you're not an achievement hunter. You're gonna get pissed at times, but that's when you go to another game. When you're burnt out on everything you have, this is a nice option to default to.

I enjoy this game, and I'm the type to play exclusively online PvPs. Me liking single player / offline content is pretty rare, but Clone Drone seemed to have slipped through the radar this time. If the game seems interesting, I'd snatch it whenever it's on sale. There's a lot of replayability in this title and it's a great game to grind.

As an objective rating, I'd give this a || [B]6/10[/B] ||.
If you like legos, you should like Clone Drone in the Danger Zone.

review: I really liked this one. Clever campaign, it is short (so it doesn't overstay its welcome), has some clever elements, and takes a little bit skill that you develop over the many "humans" that will meet their demise to the flaming swords and gigantic hammers of the jet-pack jumping robots. Suffer the quick wit and witticisms of the robot commander overlord and his bantering bunch as they commentate your successes and failures, life after pathetic human life. If you like "sandbox" battling and robot takeover jokes you will LOVE this. I enjoyed the combat... it isn't that long so if you aren't the type of person to finish games, casually give this a go a knock a title out in your library.

author: {'steamid': '76561198080146170', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 13, 'playtime_forever': 4774, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4529, 'last_played': 1700814513}
review:
Clone Drone in the Danger Zone is a combat-focused horde fighting game. You play as a human converted into a robot body and are pitted against hundreds of various enemies in a practically endless arena. Personally, I love this game.

One thing I look for in a combat-focused game is a deep and intricate combat system. At first, this game's combat system seems pretty simple. Sword hit enemy = dead. Easy, right? Then you learn about things like blocking, parrying, armour-bypassing, the difference between side strikes against different enemies, and suddenly it becomes a lot more complicated. Then you realise there are four (maybe five) weapons that CAN be used in isolation, but can also be combined with your other weapons, and all of a sudden the combat system feels a lot more complicated. There's a lot to learn, and while the skill floor is very low (since anyone can grasp the basics of this game's sword combat, it's really simple), the skill ceiling is incredibly high. What's even better is that they didn't need to include any combo system in the game, making it much less daunting to players new to combat systems.

Another important thing in combat-focused games is the enemies. Clone Drone in the Danger Zone has a whole host of enemy types, each stronger than the last and carrying various weapons. What makes the enemies even more fun to fight is that each robot sports its own AI. The lower tier ones just run at you in a straight line. However, the higher tier ones move almost like actual players, requiring a great amount of skill to overcome.

Onto the graphics. It takes a voxel-based approach since slicing and dicing robots is a big part of the game. It's quite satisfying to melt away a robot by slamming a hammer into them, or cut up a robot with a laser sword. The colours can be a tad bit flat at times, but the game still looks amazing.

The music is also stellar. There are a whole host of tracks that convey different emotions. From intense combat, to fear, to heroism, etc. Although, it can get a bit repetitive at one point, especially the arena music that plays constantly throughout the survival mode and in parts of the campaign mode.

Finally, there's the story. Clone Drone in the Danger Zone has a campaign mode comprised of five chapters. The story itself is quite exciting, and has its fair share of twists and turns. However, I felt as if it did end on a bit of a "not sure" note. It absolutely didn't have a bad ending, but the ending didn't feel extremely satisfying. It felt a bit rushed. Although, it didn't detract too much from the overall story.

In the end, Clone Drone in the Danger Zone is a fantastic horde-based fighting game with a lot of depth and fun to be had. Whether you like slicing enemies, taking them from afar, feeling like a hero, or designing your own levels, there's always classic fun to be had in the robot arena.

Gameplay: 9 / 10
Story: 6.5 / 10
Graphics: 7 / 10
Music: 9 / 10

Final Score: 7.8 / 10 (Great)

author: {'steamid': '76561198080818788', 'num_games_owned': 315, 'num_reviews': 42, 'playtime_forever': 11312, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 918, 'last_played': 1707220171}
review:
Yes one of the best games I have ever played.

A game of pure skill. I am actually not the best at hand eye coordination but still, every death feels fair. Simple game loop will never get old. Lots of stuff to do in single player which is a + for me. It has the old skool feel of, a game that was designed to be fully finished with out extra stuff. And lots to do with the basic interactions in the game. It has a great level editor which seems to allow for scripted events. Some very good levels out there. Story is nice. Challenge modes are great. Endless mode is there to live out whatever over powered set of upgrades you dream of trying together, but only if you are skilled enough the clear enough endless levels to get them all.  (my top score is like 23 lvls right now). 

Voxel characters allow for a gameplay with no HP mechanics. You die when your head/torso is destroyed, or both legs or if you lose the ability to attack. I used to think both arms counted but if you have flamebreath you can actually continue with out arms. Once I cleared a level with only one leg left by hopping around and breathing fire on enemies. 

Good soundtrack. All voices are text to speech, but good text to speech that is funny to listen to. As such anyone can create custom dialogue for the game. 

There is MP, I have not tried it. Duels are private lobbies only for example. 

Basically infinite replay value. Amazing game play. Unique.. there is nothing light it really that I have played before. Art style that will always look good. Amazing price range. I actually bought two copies but the guy I gave it to found it too hard. His son likes it though, but would feel weird playing with some internet friends son who I have never met. So I'll probably pick up another copy for someone else at somepoint. That's the good thing about its pricing, I could happily buy this game 4 times and not feel ripped off.

review: Ive played clone drone for about a total of 3 days across 2 weeks, i feel like the difficulty curve isnt bad and the story mode is fun to play for a few hours then you beat it. About 3-4 hours for a new player and maybe 1-2 for a better player (def not me that's for sure) getting the game to 100% has so far been a fun grind! About 82% of the way there. My only complaint is the Last Bot Standing mode, the way people play and the way the levels are made make it not very fun, I do think with practice it can be fun but I myself do not feel like it is worth my time. As for the price tag? its a bit much but its mostly worth it.

review:
Commentatron

Commentatron is one of the robots in the duo that makes up the commentators. Only the top half of his torso is visible, as he is behind a table. He has a deep, dark voice. He is a robot with a rather large chest, resembling a muscular man. He has a black suit, headset, red eyes, and reddish hair accessories. As his name suggests, he will usually make comments on what the player is doing and what the outcome of the level was. He will often wave his arms around while speaking, and is notably more expressive than Analysis-bot, he views the user and watches him burn
In one of his lines, Commentatron asks Analysis-bot what his relationship with Purple Shep is, referencing the fact that Analysis-bot uses the same voice as Purple Shep.
In another one of his lines, Commentatron says that he loves the smell of energy swords in the morning, revealing that he has a "nose" installed.
In one of his lines, Commentatron proposed the idea that he and Analysis-bot should form a band (although he calls it a "popular musical act" due to robot speech patterns).
If you use the camera, you can see that he has legs, and has been standing up the whole time. His legs seem thin and awkward when compared to the rest of his body.
He appears to be a re-purposed mark 2 sword robot, or some sort of sword robot, presumed by his body shape.
In chapter 4, he can be seen when the human diplomat is sent to the arena to "negotiate."

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Analysis-bot

"Soon all the humans will be garbage!"

Analysis-bot is one of the robots in the duo that make up the commentators. Due to his small size, he sits on the table that Commentatron stands behind. He has no limbs at all, black coat, green eyes and accessories, and as the name suggests, he will often analyze what the player is doing and the upcoming level, occasionally answering questions from Commentatron.
In the ending cutscene of chapter 3, we get a look inside one of the Harvester Fleet ships. Inside, we see what appears to be a command center, with four robots that are the same model as Analysis-bot, just with military uniforms and different eye pieces. In chapter 4, they are revealed to be ship officers, specifically Logistics, Warfare, Mind Space, and Infantry.
In one line, Commentatron asks Analysis-bot about his relationship with Purple Shep. Analysis-bot quickly responds with "I don't know Purple Shep! We are not best friends!‚Äù
However, in another line, when Commentatron asks him about Purple Shep, he replies that they share the same voice modulator.
During the Random upgrade challenge, he mentions that if he had arms, he would like them to be the same as Upgrade bot's.
The Harvester ship officers had emergency combat modes, which included flight, flamethrowers, shooting arrows from their mouths, charging at the player, and sword wielding (although they needed to use their mouths to do so). It is unknown if Analysis Bot has these abilities as well.
In Chapter 4, Analysis-bot can be briefly seen when the human diplomat is sent to the arena to "negotiate."
Analysis-bot is apparently a big fan of Spider-Tron 5000 and Spider-Tron 6000. In one quote he says that "[he] likes robots that analyse things!
In multiple lines during story and endless mode, we are shown that Analysis-bot displays an interest in poetry. Some of his lines follow some sort of rhyme scheme, usually followed by commentatron applauding his poetic abilities.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Commentators

The Commentators are a duo of robots who add colorful comments (Red being Commentration bot and Green being Analysis bot) before and after each battle. They do not comment during battle unless a Spidertron gets cut by a saw blade or the player hits their booth. The Commentators give information on the upcoming level and make remarks about the chosen upgrades. These are often humorous, sarcastic, or even rude. The commentators are displayed on screens on each wall of the arena, and on four screens in the upgrade area. If the player manages to get up to their booth in the arena, a force field will blast the player back. The Commentators cannot be harmed. Their true thoughts on the player is unknown, as they appear to want to see the player die at one point, and at other points, they appear to favor the player. The commentatrion bot did not tell analysis bot that he had a nose installed!!


Trivia
When using photo mode inside the commentators box, you can see that Commentatron is standing on a thin ledge with the end of his toes.

On the nintendo switch varyient on one level commentstron say spider tro on instead of just spider tron if you listen closely

-----------------------------------------

review:
Great game with both pros and cons.

If you plan just playing the game to get through its content, it has a story mode with 5 chapters along with some challenges. Fun but can be finished pretty quickly.

However, this game has some of the best PVP melee combat I've ever played. The slicing and dicing, smashing and kicking, It's all very satisfying. There's a massive skill gap to climb as well. The downsides are the developers haven't given any sign of expanding on this. There is only a small battle royale mode and option to private duel your friends. Occasional hackers in last bot standing. And you wont find a game past midnight in your region.

There is a lot of changes and additions the game badly needs but it's too fun to not recommend.

author: {'steamid': '76561199473450747', 'num_games_owned': 233, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 785, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 623, 'last_played': 1706776102}
review:
As a seasoned game reviewer on Steam, I've had the opportunity to explore a wide variety of games. One such intriguing title that I have recently been indulging in is "Clone Drone in the Danger Zoo". 

First and foremost, the unique premise of this game provides a refreshing perspective in the overcrowded genre of action games. As the name suggests, you control a clone drone, battling against a horde of dangerous creatures in a high-risk zoo. The concept itself incites a sense of thrill and engages players right from the get-go.

The gameplay mechanics of "Clone Drone in the Danger Zoo" stand out as a strong point. The combat system is robust, well-executed, and remarkably intuitive, relying heavily on timing, strategy, and a keen understanding of the enemy's behaviors. The clone drone's ability to swap between different weapons adds a further layer of complexity and keeps the gameplay intriguing.

Visually, the game does a commendable job. The graphics, while not photorealistic, have their charm, presenting a unique style that perfectly complements the game's atmosphere. Each creature is distinctively designed, and the varied environments of the zoo add a considerable depth to the visual experience.

However, the game does come with its own set of flaws. For one, the difficulty curve tends to be inconsistent, with some battles abruptly more challenging than others. This could potentially lead to moments of frustration for players. Furthermore, while the game's AI is generally competent, there are moments when the creatures' behaviors become slightly predictable, reducing the challenge in later stages.

Despite these shortcomings, the game's replayability factor is worth noting. The variety of creatures, environments, and weapons allows for different strategies and approaches, making each playthrough unique.

In conclusion, "Clone Drone in the Danger Zoo" is a worthwhile experience for those seeking a unique, action-packed game. Its innovative premise, engaging gameplay mechanics, and distinct visual style offer a delightful package for action-game enthusiasts. While there are areas for improvement, particularly in difficulty balancing and AI behavior, the overall enjoyment of the game is not significantly hampered. If you're in search of a fresh take on the action genre, I would certainly recommend giving "Clone Drone in the Danger Zoo" a try.

review: Very fun but can be hard but once you complete it, it is the best feeling but overall no complaints. It's very fun and it is by far one of my favourite games of all time.  There is a mode on singleplayer called challenge mode and it is definitely my favourite because you can complete them and for some you unlock a new upgrade to get from upgrade bot during matches like one I will mention later (endless mode).  There are other challenges that just unlock trophies which i really like and my favourite being the inferno challenge trophy but my favourite challenge probably being the laser only challenge or the hammer only challenge due to the laser one being so unique and the hammer one i just liked smashing everything.  It is also fun to play with friends on multiplayer with lots of fun and hard challenges like the ones from singleplayer but instead changed so its harder for you and your friends to have more fun instead of it just being too easy, but if you are like me and have no friends you can still get the rewards from multiplayer by playing it by yourself but it is a lot harder.  Or you can just join a random public game.  My personal favourite challenges from multiplayer are probably the zombie challenge due to it being fun and unique and the random upgrade challenge since it was always unpredictable due to the random upgrades and random levels.  I also love the story modes (no spoilers) and if you play it on insane difficulty you get special rewards for completing each chapter but beware they are very hard and can be frustrating.  There are 3 more modes to talk about 1 of them being endless mode.  Endless mode is on both singleplayer and multiplayer and is just as it sounds it goes on endlessly until you die.  The second mode i haven't mentioned is only on multiplayer called last bot standing.  It is a fun mode where you and other real people fight off and see who is the best human out of the rest.  The last mode is one i haven't tried out yet due to me not streaming on twitch if i would stream it would be on Youtube but I just tend not to anyway.  The mode is called twitch mode where i think you can bet what bot will kill the streamer? I'm not really sure.

author: {'steamid': '76561198446175113', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 10, 'playtime_forever': 5737, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4926, 'last_played': 1699062157}
review:
I used to like this game, but after trying to play insanity on story mode, it enlightened me on the flaws of this game. Many things caused my dislike of the game, like striking an opening in an armored opponent and the game making the sword phase through the body to hit the armor on the other side of the body from which you sliced. Or that sometimes your weapon will just not do any damage when the enemy seems to not have this issue. Or the possibility that the enemy is programmed to have an unfair advantage in other parts than size or weaponry, such as cutting an enemy with a flame sword could cause a slight burn if you only did a scratch. If the enemy scratches you the same way, you instantly combust into flames. I also somewhat confirmed that enemy's have an unfair resistance seeing that earlier an archer bot lost his entire right side of his body and was still running around [they're supposed to die if they're unable to use their weapons]. There's also the inconsistency in how you can die, some times a wittle boo-boo on your torso and head has your character instantly dropping dead. Then there are times where you're missing all but a small corner of your head, having a hole through your chest from an arrow and STILL chugging along perfectly fine. Then there is insanity, which is just complete anarchy. Game design? pffffft, whats that? I don't even consider this a challenge, it's straight up unfair and requires luck beyond my comprehension to beat. It highlights all the problems with the game with a very disgusting bow on top. It feels like it wants me to beat it competitively in a game where precise moves that requires nano-second inputs are something that straight up doesn't exist as every attack is sloppy, has huge delays and annoying quirks [probably due to the animations]. It makes me crazy as there are so many moments my sword SHOULD HAVE done damage if only the sword continued to do damage for another half second, 

I can go on and on about this, but it's time I cut to the point.

Don't buy this game, it isn't worth your time. 

If you buy it and give it your time, expect to encounter a frustrating dead end where you'll probably realize that you should've listened to me.

review:
El juego consiste en batallas de robots en una arena, fin.
si vamos mas profundo el juego cuenta con un modo historia bastante entretenido en mi opinion.
Cuentas con diversas armas y mejoras como una espada, un arco, una maza, una lanza y mejoras como mayor velocidad o mejoras que se implementan normalmente a tus armas, como una flecha mas grande, un escudo para tu lanza o un martillo mas enorme

frenetico y divertido, lo recomiendo si no sabes que jugar en un sabado por la tarde, personalmente me termine la historia una ma√±ana, sinceramente me quede viciada.

Si buscas algo divertido que jugar con amigos pues tambien sirve ya que cuenta con un online medianamente activo/muerto, lo suficiente como para que jueges con otros igualmente, y cuenta con una opcion de duelos privados para asi poder luchar con amigos 1v1. 

en mi experiencia aun no eh jugado con amigos... a ninguno le gusta o le interesa JSJS

review: This game offers an interesting story, fun challenges, a great co-op mode selection AND a way to make your own maps! (You can also customize yourself sorta. You'll get options in the multiplayer option in settings/options.)  The spear is a good long range weapon if you prefer distance combat. The sword is pretty much a decent all rounder as it can deflect arrows with an upgrade and is good for close combat (duh), the hammer is great for smashing. And the bow is great for distance work if you dislike close quarters combat. Highly recommend for those who are interested in fighting games like this! (There's also achievements. Go wild completionists)

review: Its a good SINGLEPLAYER game. This game I do recommend for singleplayer but the multiplayer is easily the worst I've played. It's like trying to play Asia servers from US Central. The story is good, the singleplayer modes are all great, but no matter what I do online is the ultimate pain experience. Kicking your balls has nothing on the teleporting arrows, spidertrons, and hammers of coop mode. And that's not to even MENTION friendlies teleporting into your line of fire. If laggy without a teammate was kicking your balls with a 100 pound sledgehammer, then doing it with a teammate is childbirth.

review:
Pretty fun, has hard challenges, a level editor (and therefore workshop levels), and is in general pretty fun and difficult. Definitely recommend you play this, and do me a favour and try out everything and go for the achievements

Edit: This game is still pretty fun. Only one problem regarding the achievements. The Achievement "Hello Doborog" is really hard to get in my region because 1. The devs usually stream at a time where it's already 3 AM for me and 2. If they ever stop streaming, it will be impossible to get that achievement (Unless they'll release a final update that gives you the achievement automatically)
But all in all, very good game, can recommend.

author: {'steamid': '76561198341022151', 'num_games_owned': 134, 'num_reviews': 23, 'playtime_forever': 20347, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20278, 'last_played': 1702362063}
review:
In the name of Allah, the Most Merciful, the Most Compassionate, I come forth to share my thoughts on "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone." Verily, this game has brought me much joy and amusement, yet it bears certain elements that do not resonate with my personal taste. Nevertheless, I wholeheartedly recommend it for its captivating mechanics and its ability to provide solace in moments of relaxation.

Firstly, let us discuss the matter of the soundtrack. Whilst the game boasts an intriguing array of mechanical marvels, the dubstep-inspired melodies, albeit skillfully composed, do not align with my devout inclinations. It is but a personal preference, for which I offer no reproach to the creators. Each soul finds solace in different harmonies, and it is mine humble wish that future endeavors may cater to a wider spectrum of musical tastes.

Another aspect that I feel compelled to address is the perceived "Soy Reddit air" that lingers within the game. As a devout follower of the Islamic faith, I seek environments that cultivate virtues of dignity, respect, and modesty. Although the game may exhibit certain elements that may be incongruous with my sensibilities, I bear no ill will towards the creators, for it is their artistic expression. I do implore them, however, to consider diversifying the themes and dialogues to appeal to a broader range of players, encompassing varying cultural and spiritual backgrounds.

Notwithstanding these observations, "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone" shines brightly with its captivating gameplay and intriguing mechanics. The thrill of facing formidable adversaries, wielding weapons with precision, and honing one's reflexes brings delight to one's heart. The variety of challenges, such as the duels, waves, and even the chance to control a mighty spider robot, fosters an immersive experience that captivates the mind and nourishes the spirit.

This game serves as a sanctuary, a respite from the trials of the day. The ability to unwind and immerse oneself in the thrilling world of robotic combat is a blessing indeed. It offers an opportunity to detach from worldly concerns and indulge in moments of leisure, allowing the mind to find solace and rejuvenation.

In conclusion, "Clone Drone in the Danger Zone" is a captivating arena of robotic battle, though it bears certain elements that may not align with my devout beliefs. I extend my sincere recommendation to all seeking an engaging experience, for its mechanics and gameplay are truly commendable. Let us embrace the diversity of artistic expression while offering feedback to shape future creations that encompass the values we hold dear. May Allah guide us in all our endeavors and grant us tranquility as we embark on our digital adventures.

review:
Pros: The gameplay in Clone Drone is fun and unique. I haven't heard of another game that has voxel-based combat. When you play it is fun and satisfying to cut down the robots. The game has an interesting story that adds new mechanics which keep it unique compared to the rest of the game. The game also has a ton of different challenges both in single-player and multiplayer. They don't get boring since they have different premises and because of the fun combat system.

Neutral: The insanity difficulties for the story mode can be a bit too difficult for chapters 2 and 5, they could be a bit easier. Some of the secret achievements are too obscure and need to be found using a guide.

review: I kinda would like to recommend this. But the lag there often is which makes you wonder why you died, quite often is keeping me from it. It can be very frustrating when you die because of lag, which will be most of your deaths after you learned how to play this. There's no chat, so you'll just look incapable. I've been pulled through some challenges, and I have pulled a few fellows through challenges. Singleplayer Campaign on the other hand is a blast. The humor is cool and it all flows very well. It's got the potential to be a nice Multiplayer Co-op game, but it isn't quite there, yet. PvP is, well, hit and miss. The laggy situation makes it a total gamble.

review: Ich habe das game im sale, mit unrailed und paint the town red(alle3sch√∂negelegenheitsspiele) geschossen und muss sagen, dass mir der storymodus viel spass bereitet hat. Zur story: Die menscheit wird von roboter-alien √ºberfallen, um den menschlichen verstand in roboterk√∂rper zu stopfen. In arenak√§mpfen tritt man dann gegen roboter-alien an. Sobald du zerst√∂rt wurderst wird der aktuelle verstand gel√∂scht und man startet mit  neuen verstand in einen neuen roboter und verliert alle upgrades, Die reste werden unter dem spot von analyse-bot und komentar-tron aus der arena gekehrt. Wer die ersten 2 level mit je 10 runden √ºbersteht, wird aus der permadeath-h√∂lle entlassen und die wahre story beginnt.  Ich habe ca 10 h (geht auch schneller) gebraucht f√ºr die story. Im endlosmodus kann man seine skillz immer wieder testen und mit dem online coopmodus holt man sich freunde oder fremde mit ins boot. Den battleroyalmodus habe ich noch nicht getestet, ist aber auch vorhanden und heisst"last bot standing".. Im sale eine totale empfehlung

review:
Clone drone in the danger zone,
A game that's truly in a class alone,
Where metal warriors fight to the bone,
And the player's skills are constantly honed.

The visuals are sleek, like polished chrome,
And the action's so intense, you'll feel in a cyclone,
Enemies attack from every side and zone,
But you'll keep fighting, never to bemoan.

Combat's your weapon, your defense, your cornerstone,
Use swords, axes, and hammers to smite foes unknown,
And with every victory, you'll steadily enthrone,
A champion, skilled and battle-hardened, like a milestone.

All in all, Clone drone in the danger zone,
Is a game that you won't play and simply disown,
Its thrilling gameplay and challenge will enthrone,
Your heart and soul, leaving you in a rhyming tone.

8/10 A good mix between goofy interactions and themes, and serious difficulty.

Best,

author: {'steamid': '76561198006806303', 'num_games_owned': 799, 'num_reviews': 156, 'playtime_forever': 73, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 20, 'last_played': 1682151471}
review:
Here is the first 15 minutes: https://youtu.be/4oGOkLSaqgw

Clone Drone in the Danger Zone (CDDZ) is a side-splitting, rib-tickling, robo-romp that'll leave you in stitches! Let's start with 3 pros and 1 con that sum up this comedic chaos.

Pro #1: The game's hilariously absurd premise has you controlling robot clones, slicing and dicing through arenas like a tin-can samurai on a caffeine high. It's the perfect blend of futuristic mayhem and slapstick humor.

Pro #2: With razor-sharp wit, the game's commentators deliver punchlines with the precision of a laser-guided sword. You'll be laughing so hard, you'll hardly notice your own gruesome, dismembered limbs scattered across the arena floor.

Pro #3: CDDZ's challenging gameplay is the cherry on top of this humor sundae, adding a sense of accomplishment to your metallic massacre. Surviving each wave of enemies feels like a well-earned badge of honor (or a really twisted joke).

Con #1: The only downside? You might end up with an uncontrollable urge to punt your Roomba across the living room after playing.

In conclusion, Clone Drone in the Danger Zone is a gut-busting, laugh-a-minute adventure that combines the best of robot combat, witty banter, and a difficulty curve that'll keep you coming back for more. Just remember to give your household appliances a reassuring pat after each gaming session.

English:

Oh no, sorry to hear you are experiencing bad lag in the game! We are regularly working on improving the multiplayer lag / feel and would love to learn if there are opportunities to improve the game's multiplayer networking.

Could you reach out to support@doborog.com and we can investigate further?

Some things to try:
- Does this happen for every game match, or just some? 
- Ensure your game is connecting to the closest region. You can try forcing the region to connect to in the multiplayer settings. What sort of ping do you see?
- Are you behind a software firewall or firewall in your country? Do you get a better latency with other games?
- Are you using a VPN to connect to matches? This can potentially add extra latency. If there are other regions available for your VPN, see if there is one closer to you or the game server region.

Let me know if nothing helps and we can investigate further.

- Brian

review: how is it i can lose my left arm and my leg yet one scratch to the right and i die like that also the ally robots keep trying to kill me
developer_response:
I totally get you, it can def be frustrating to feel like you're losing for no reason. Some context from behind the scenes, just so you get a feel for what's going on: the robot bodies are exclusively right-handed, so if your right hand bites it, you can't hold weapons anymore and you get restarted. (Kick can be a good thing to mitigate this! If you haven't tried it, I recommend.)

That doesn't necessarily make it not frustrating sometimes though. Is there a particular time that stands out when your right arm took some damage that felt like it shouldn't be a big deal, but then you died seemingly outta nowhere? I'd love to hear about it. (You can reach me at support@doborog.com ). We're always looking for feedback to better tune things

author: {'steamid': '76561198336968828', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 9849, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 71, 'playtime_at_review': 5842, 'last_played': 1711633622}
review:
"This game is really fun. The gameplay is amazing, and the controls are really good. You really feel like you control your character, and they absolutely nailed the feeling of slicing the enemies into pieces. Also, the narrator's humor was pretty funny. There is a nice variety of weapons, enemies, and different levels and challenges, so you never get tired of this game, especially when you play it with friends. Although the multiplayer can be better. The story mode was pretty good and entertaining, but I wanted to get more out of the spaceship mechanics."

Overall, I would rate it 8.5/10

chapter 5 final boss insane difficulty, is the wost boss ive EVER FOUGHT, its only based on RNG, and nothing else, up to this point, in my 115 hours of playing, ive had immense fun playing this game, after trying to fight that boss, i dont even want to see this game anymore, i dont know if i will ever come back, please balance that boss here some suggestions:

give the player a normal bow, without any upgrades

make the ally respawn after death after some time

give the player 3 energy

make the player be able to pick its weapon before fighting

make the drones move slightly slower than the player, becausee it is the most annoying part of fighting the boss, almost being able to hit them, but not quite.

author: {'steamid': '76561198261914332', 'num_games_owned': 199, 'num_reviews': 14, 'playtime_forever': 1426, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1331, 'last_played': 1703960799}
review:
So, I've been playing the game for a while now and I can say, that it's a pretty good one. I mean, it's nothing special or so, but it just got that feeling of being made with much love and diligence :)

Story is fine. There are some cool mechanics that are story only. So it's a cool mixup to the maingame.

The graphics are good for the game.

The gameplay can be repetitive, but you can try out different playstyles and that's where the game is shining. I'm not recommending the online mode though, anyone is tryharding and I had no fun playing it, but you got enough offline modes to play instead. These modes are in a nutshell all the same (killing a wave of robots that get more difficult and versatile the further you get) but the true challange, is to get actually good in it. You got so much elements you can try out and so many different enemys you are encountering. 
It won't get boring that fast in my oppinion.

All in all, it's a nice little game for anyone. I'm recommending the game for the full price. And if it's on sale, just buy it. Don't think about it. It's worth

review: This game is loads of fun. I play on Steam with a n xbox controller and it's quickly become one of my favorites. Challenging but easy enough to get into and learn. Dig the skin and voice customization options and odd menu of pre-scripted lines you can choose from to say to other players. My only complaint is when you're back is against a wall, your head fills up the screen blocking out most of your view which isn't realistic at all. Seems like this could be improved somehow. It's not necessary to Zoom when your back is against wall. Not sure if this is a design standard (I don't play FPS games much) or an odd choice by the makers. It's still one of the most fun games I've come across!

author: {'steamid': '76561198976199738', 'num_games_owned': 66, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 3894, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 1, 'playtime_at_review': 3109, 'last_played': 1711841398}
review:
Amazing game that never gets old :)
The graphics are meh 8/10
FPS is 10/10
Server and ping in multiplayer is 7.5/10
Community 10/10
And the workshop levels are awesome :)
The wide and large variety of challenges makes it even more fun and pumps the game up more for when it gets boring,i overall recommend it as it's quite worth the price. It can get very annoying when you can't do a challenge but i managed to do more than 5 in solo and all in multiplayer.
So overall it is a 9/10 game,i find it very fun to play with friends and the map creator or adventure creator,whatever you wanna call it is pretty neat,large variety of access to such things in the game. However,I do wish that we can have a proper chat to type into,as the emoting and things aren't very "functional" at communication with allies. It can get confusing and allies might not get what you say and screw the level up causing you to fail. I also wish that we could make game mods (Like Custom Weapons,Custom avatars,or functions)

review:
It's a great game, very fun, but it'd be a lot better if it had a build for Linux. The game was made with Unity game engine, and it has a built-in option for Linux builds, it takes literally one single button press to export to Linux.

Running it with Proton is a problem, since it has a memory leak and the game become unplayable after some time.

And having a native build for Linux would make it a lot easier for Steam Deck users to play the game without any problems.

author: {'steamid': '76561198317674509', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 8330, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3880, 'last_played': 1705460780}
review:
This game is amazing. The combat can be a bit tricky at times, but once you figure out which weapons and upgrades work best for each enemy bot, then you're golden. The story mode is simple: nothing special but nothing bad.
     The main gameplay is the endless mode, where you fight wave after wave, battlefield after battlefield of enemies, getting harder and better with each tier advancement. You pick upgrades, from mobility, to a kick, to three other weapons. I'm trying to get all the upgrades for the achievement, and I still haven't gotten them all at 67 hours of play. Sure, running out of clones leaves you back at the start, but I'm still playing and still having fun.
     There's also multiplayer, be it doing online challenges, or the free-for-all. There's not many people playing at a time, but there's also very little lag. It's good if you want a quick online experience.
     I'd highly recommend this. My only issue is that I don't think I can get the twitch achievement due to the person I'm supposed to watch hasn't streamed in two months at this point. If they make it so that you can get the achievement when anyone on Dogborg streams, or maybe make it not mandatory to complete the game to 100%, then that'd be great.

author: {'steamid': '76561199155021686', 'num_games_owned': 79, 'num_reviews': 13, 'playtime_forever': 1941, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1850, 'last_played': 1708457292}
review:
This game is good in some places, really. For once, I enjoyed playing this game for a long time.
Game is easy to master, and easy to learn and read.
Great AI, And good mechanics.

But something's off. You know, When I heard this game had a campaign, I felt happy So I bought it.
Expecting a thrilling, Great, Amazing game play experience in campaign... When I finished all of the chapters...
I was a bit disappointing.
Now, you could go into the comment section and talk about how the campaign is good, But I am speaking from MY opinion.
Now, when I first started campaign, it started off good. Plain old game play, I got a bit bored then.
Then, I completed level 10, an then, a Robot just came out and disabled the force field.
Hey, Listen. If the robot tech is SO advanced in This universe, how did a random robot just come and disabled the force field? Don't you think the other robots could have done something? 

I mean, if there's some LORE, or something i'm missing out on- Please do tell me!
Chapter 2 was good... The levels had gotten a bit harder, 
(Especially with the addition of hammer bots, kick bots, And more), but the thing is..

The end of the chapter- Is quite confusing.
There's this harvesting thing that is supposedly "Harvesting" all of the humans, to be sent into the danger zone, or something.

And then the garbage bots just pick you up and just carries me and takes me back to the human I played before?
I mean, It makes sense, It's probably just the work of the robot that sabotaged the barrier.

And well, I don't feel like writing my review's for the rest of the chapters, but the rest of the chapters are decent and confusing, so Kudo's to the developer's.

But I liked the game, but I dislike the campaign a little.
If you enjoy robots, action, and fighter games, This one's for you.

So what do I give on campaign? 6.7/10. The rest of the game? 7.9 out of ten.

So, For my review on the rest of the game.
I like the rest of the game. Sorta.
It has endless mode, Some challenges you can do (if you get bored of slicing robots).
I feel like this game has Much, Much, MORE potential, and that this game could be better and expanded on.

So, I enjoy the game in some way.
If I could change a part of this game, I would make the campaign a bit more understandable.
Then again, that's just my opinion, and you should respect it. (If anyone has the merit to do so.)

author: {'steamid': '76561198315083380', 'num_games_owned': 144, 'num_reviews': 19, 'playtime_forever': 523, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 503, 'last_played': 1695661967}
review:
Rese√±a en espa√±ol

Es un buen juego, las 4 o 5 armas que tienes estan bastante buenas para pelear junto a las mejoras correspondientes de cada una, los graficos estan buenos y la historia esta bien pero no hay mucho que decir, las cosas negativas serian la repetitividad de los niveles osea se que es por la historia pero hubiera sido algo mejor si los niveles fueran mas aleatorios para que no se vuelva aburrido jugarlo a lo largo y el soundtrack del juego es muy monotono(literalmente son 1 o 2 canciones casi todo el rato excepto en otros lugares pero no es mucho el cambio) pero dentro de todo es buen juego, si lo quieres comprar yo lo recomendaria en una oferta si o si.

English Review

Its a good game, the 4 or 5 weapons the game gives you are pretty good to fight with each upgrade for the corresponding weapon, the visuals are ok and the story is fine but not much to say about it, the negative of this game are the repeatability of the levels, i know is because for the sake of the story mode but in the long run it becomes very monotonous it will be nice if  the game had more randomness and the soundtrack of the game leaves to much to be desired (literally is one or two songs for almost all the fights in the arena) in other places changes a little but not too much but overall is a good game, if you want to pick it, pick it on sale.

author: {'steamid': '76561198994051065', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 9495, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 9204, 'last_played': 1705514678}
review:
Great game with a very unique concept and an even more unique mechanic, the story is well... a story but it is interesting to say the least and there is so much content afterwards like the challenges witch are a great place to start in learing the game¬¥s scaling dificulty and weapons.

Endless is self explanatory, you can complete the campaign in harder difficulties and achievement hunting and multiplayer is super fun with poeple that greet you and help you with the emotes to people who try to say the are better than you but the emote system is it¬¥s own filter and it just makes them look dumb. The first thing i dislike is the battle royal gamemode thing where you just get thrown into an arena and fight actual people, but, i don¬¥t know how complicated it is to make some sort of skill ranking thing like csgo so i shouldn¬¥t judge a book by its cover but what i can say is that a lot of sweats play that mode and it can frustrate and discorauge you like it did to me.

the second thing i dislike a little less is the mountaion you need to climb after getting to know everything the game has to offer since when you get to the highest difficulty you have a lot to learn and memorize to then apply that into idk, that arena gamemode?

I love the level creator, i have made a lot of levels in the re-use style that the devs made for the endless mode and the system is so clean that if you want to start making levels all you need to do is let your imagination (and balancing logic) do the rest for you, and maybe some tutorials but i never used those and i have sone really good levels but i mostly keep them to myself to have more endgame content.

This game is for you IF you stick to it, since studies and a brutal year have made me forget the game. But it is still fun after a year of playing

review:
Giving this game a 78/100 (7.8/10)

Pros: good game, fun, good upgrades, good difficulty incline, good weapons, fun campaign, and just fun to play over and over again

Cons: Buggy, A bit pricey for what it is, weapons hit box is a bit bigger than the weapon, encountered a few bugs, and damage system is a little weird to me.

Overall, i will say that even though it has these cons and bugs, i would still recommend playing this game, game is amazingly made.

author: {'steamid': '76561199230096112', 'num_games_owned': 34, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 715, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 428, 'last_played': 1694306626}
review:
No hago rese√±as en juegos, pero este lo merece.

Gran juego, con todas las letras. la historia es buena, enganchante a mi parecer, lastima que dura poco.
Tiene buena jugabilidad, te puede costar las primeras batallas si no tienes experiencia en el juego, pero cuando le agarras la mano se te vuelve facil controlar las armas.
Buenas mecanicas de juego, lo que se rompan partes del cuerpo de tu personaje al recibir un ataque en esa parte es magnifico, y juega con que no te mueras de un simple golpe ( dependiendo el lugar en donde recibas el ataque ), tambien puedo mencionar que considero muy bien el tema de la patada, que puedes obtener como mejora, se pueden crear buenas estrategias con esta.
Tiene bastante rejugabilidad, posee desafios que te enganchan y te insitan a mejorar para superarlos, el modo "sin fin" tiene aleatoridad en sus mapas, por lo que nunca sera lo mismo en cada partida, cosa que quita monotonia.
El unico punto en contra que noto es que el online tiene poca gente.

Ademas es tiene robots con espadas laser, que mas queres flaco?, compralo
Nota final:  8,5/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198379230760', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 81, 'playtime_forever': 2562, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 37, 'last_played': 1698498665}
review:
NEW Zombie single player challenge: 
Yeah I just beat the new challenge level today with no ROBOT HANDS!! One of the zombies swiped my hands off and so I had to kill the boss with spike traps and with my kick upgrade lol. Crazy! I thought I soft locked myself there and I would have to restart but thankfully I didn't need to do that! Jetpack zombies were easy to take out with the kicks and spike traps too. But I did notice audio problems when I died close to the start of the level. Like the friendly and non friendly npcs were 'offline' and not doing anything. It didn't affect the progress of the game though! So glad that was not a soft lock. Thanks for adding the solo zombie challenge level!! Kind of mad how the ending kind of adds more to the story which is cool to see!

Newer Review: 
Game is still great and highly repayable but I am not a huge fan of the battle royal game because of how over powered the fire in the game is. If the devs were to remove fire weapon upgrades from the battle royal I would actually try playing it.

I personally prefer playing the offline modes more than the multiplayer but it can be very fun if you are playing co op in a group fighting against smart robot AI!!! Co op is great but battle royal not so much. 

The story is good too but nothing too expansive! The final boss is great!! Was fun to cut that monster into pieces.

Zombie mode was a nice bonus in this game but I wish there was a offline version of it which isn't only for co op.. Devs could you add a zombie mode for solo challenges? Would be quite nice!

I fully recommend this game btw. Good spent money! Almost endless replay-ability and it can run on the Steam Deck at full 60fps too!

Old review where I had only 5.1 hours in this game:

One of the fun fighting games I've ever played. I first played the demo and beat it without losing.. But they did use a death star laser on me once they realised they couldn't kill me the normal way.. I'm glad they made a demo for this game. It would have taken me years to finally decide if this game is worth my money. Actually it did. It really did.. I recommend this game 100%.

author: {'steamid': '76561198345843366', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 41, 'playtime_forever': 70, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 68, 'last_played': 1670518833}
review: My favorite thing about rogue-like or random combat games like this is the ability to learn and adapt with the basic tools you are given. This game doesnt have that. It doesnt matter how many times youve played, how much you know about the "Look at the enemy and decide which angle to attack with" battle mechanic, because if a single enemy, on the easiest difficulty, hits you once, you have to restart the entire run. It doesnt matter how good I am, how many times ive ran a game, if i accidentally stop paying attention to the wrong enemy, they instantly one shot me. I stop enjoying a game when i have to do the same thing with zero variety after about an hour, and ive reached past that quota, but i might revisit this review.

review: It's fine enough, but what really kills my enjoyment is that the only content after the 2-hour campaign is just permadeath roguelike bullshit, which if that wasn't enough has 10-second long gaps in between each round, in a mode where each round ends in around 15 seconds. 40% of your time in the roguelike mode is spent loading, and it's completely unnecessary too, because they could have just fade to black, etc, snap to your upgrade menu, but no, they NEED to have you walk all the way back to the entrance EVERY SINGLE TIME so that their "le ebin quirky" casters can belch out their LOLRANDOM voicelines while you take an ELEVATOR back to the spawn so you can do something that could easily have just been a menu pop-up. I bet some loser was furiously masturbating over this design choice, claiming that it's "diegetic" when really just pure tedium, not even the good kind. There's nothing stopping you from just having some drone come down to place the new voxels on your robot, why on god's green earth they went for the "immersive" option that took up 40% of your time is beyond me

review: Este juego es algo especial para m√≠, recuerdo como en el 2017 este fue uno de muchos juegos que se hizo popular por un v√≠deo que hac√≠a un youtuber conocido y como muchos ese fue mi primer contacto con esta obra de arte y tal vez creas que decirle "obra de arte" es darle mucho merito, pero es la verdad este proyecto fue hecho con pasi√≥n y esfuerzo desde el principio, contando con un modo historia entretenido y con una trama simple pero funcional adem√°s con un plot twist que no se siente anti clim√°tico porque el juego se esfuerza en presentar su humor y carisma desde los primeros minutos de juego con esos comentaristas tan esplendorosos que seguro a todos nos hubiera gustado enfrentar, en resumen este es un gran juego que con todo lo que ofrece te dar√° muchas horas de diversi√≥n y que vale absolutamente cada centavo

This game is great for both single and multiplayer modes. The workshop arenas expand the endless mode to give it greater re-playability, and the challenges are fun. You might be lucky to join an online co-op mode, and I've never done online Last Bot Standing for that reason, but if your have friends to join you, you'll have a great time in this gladiator arena. Hit boxes are pretty clear thanks to the simple design. I've had this game for about 5 years and I've watched the updates come through and only improve the game.
The only critique I have is wanting workshop maps to work in co-op endless mode, as to share the crazy maps with friends.

This game is Absolutely Awesome, I love the entire theme and the Genre of the game, Its been what I was looking for in MONTHS, and finally, It arrived. If your that type if guy who likes to fight alot in games, no matter if its single player or Multiplayer, Its for you and you can Upgrade your robot or weapon and you can Customize and create levels to play with you and your friends, Overall this game for me is a 9.5/10, I will explain why Its not a 10/10, but overall It is such an addictive game, Which can lead you to be spending Hours at your computer playing this game, anyways, It wouldn't be a 10/10 in my book because you cannot customize the actual weapon itself, but if it was able to, I would rate it a 10/10, and abit more information on the developers, Try adding coins to each chapter or level you complete so that you can use it to customize your weapons, for example, making it longer, shorter, adding cosmetics to it or even drawings on their like a mini tattoo for the weapon, so, I know this seems a bit long for this review, but On short quotes, It is a really good game you should also get it.
Graphics: Amazing
Gameplay: Good
Characters: Awesome
Details/secrets: Good

author: {'steamid': '76561198040123804', 'num_games_owned': 2265, 'num_reviews': 93, 'playtime_forever': 204, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 192, 'last_played': 1663649870}
review:
Really great game.

Combat is fun - I actually enjoyed a hack n' slash for once!!!

Characters and voice actors are great  - the two commentary robots being the best part.

9/10 game. I'll likely be returning to play Endless Mode, as the story only takes like 2-3 hours - you'll enjoy every second of it, though! 

Will def be keeping an eye on this dev in the future. I had no idea this game existed until today, but I'm glad I took the plunge and snagged it on sale.

review: The game is not the type of game i like nor dislike but i think that people should buy it if they like a challenge to make sure you can enjoy the game play the campaign it is extremely fun but on the last part in the rulers mind i could not find anything and nothing happened so sadly my game might have bugged and not loaded anything
developer_response:
Oh no!

Was it towards the section guarding the Core Instruction behind a red laser wall? To get past it you have to kill yourself on the saw blades in front of it to trigger a mind transfer into one of the guards behind it.

Or if it was a bug, exiting the game and starting up story mode again should fix it. Sorry you got stuck regardless! There's a pretty cool fight on the other end of it if you do try it again. :)

Cheers,
Erik

author: {'steamid': '76561199219255902', 'num_games_owned': 114, 'num_reviews': 42, 'playtime_forever': 2409, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 591, 'last_played': 1707851791}
review: in clone drone, your a clone. i know big shocker i was too i had to take a 30 minute breaking from this game since i pissed myself after finding out. now back to the game. you play as whoever you got from the machine, and you gotta slice and dice dudes, or smash and bash or use like a spear and go shinggg, or even a bow and go fligngnhgng. then after you finish doing that you upgrade yourself and then the dudes you were fighting get replaced by stronger dudes and cooler maps. thats the entire game. its a physics based fighting system and its a bit janky but fun. there is some stages where you are just running away from the enemys, then go in and go back to running away from enemies. the humour in this game is good but after playing it for 5 hours+ the same lines repeat. this game is really good, its got a co-op aswell, never played it since i dont got friends and it got a fortnite mode, where you play fortnite, and everyone else uses op loadouts and kills you instantly. that mode is my favourite. i would give this game a 9/10. you get what your paying for, even better if its on sale.

author: {'steamid': '76561198095508583', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 28, 'playtime_forever': 615, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 615, 'last_played': 1661538960}
review: I am a 45 yo father, probably one of the oldest people playing this game. I am a single farther to my Son, who is 14 now. My son got this game for Christmas in 2021 from his uncle, so we installed it on his computer and he started playing. By the end of the week he had 24 hours on this game. This was horrible for me, as it was already hard for me to find ways to spend time with my son, as he is always out with his friends or just watching YouTube. So I decided to make a Steam account and get this game to see if I could maybe play alongside him. I loaded into the game, picked my character and started playing but I was stuck on what you where supposed to do. I asked my Son for help and he hosted a game for me to join. I loved it as it was the best time I had spent with my Son since my wife had died. This game has ever since brought me and my son closer again and now we actually spend time together outside the house together as well. This game reminded me that there's fun to be had in everything, and it has brought both me and my Son many happy memories.
