author: {'steamid': '76561198013027602', 'num_games_owned': 292, 'num_reviews': 37, 'playtime_forever': 1873, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1861, 'last_played': 1694824664}
review:
[h1]Do the funky pillar dance![/h1]

Clone Drone in The Danger Zone is a pretty solid game where you play as [b]John Drone[/b]*, a human who has since been turned into a robot for gladiatorial entertainment by other, morally impaired robots.  Your goal is simple; Survive the arena's dangers, and maybe overthrow an evil robotic emperor while you're at it.  Or just that first one.  The plot's lightweight, and outright nonexistent in some areas, and with a game like this, it's relatively okay.  There is a Story Mode that tells a tale of resistance, and the story, while light-weight and offering a simple series of justifications for the enemy gauntlets it hurls you into, also does a great job of introducing new mechanics and weaponry in a rather natural way.
[spoiler]*Clone's name may not be John Drone[/spoiler]

Graphically, this game uses volumetric pixels, or voxels if you're not an [b]utter snob who uses fancy words.[/b]  This means 'Minecraft looks' for those who need further help, and it lends the game a blocky look that only needed a few particle effects to truly shine among the competition in that space.  Obviously, it's very readable at a glance, and with how the game plays, that's important.

Gameplay is semi-simple.  You can wield up to four weapons, a sword, a hammer, a bow, and a spear with shield.  Your goal?  Kill everything else without dying in the process.  Combat controls are simple; Swords and hammers swing where you're moving, or default to a vertical swing if you're still; Bows shoot where you're aiming, spears stab forwards at all times.  You have a dash, a jump, and with upgrades, a kick.  The game's enemies are many, varied, and vast, and all can call for different means of taking them on.  The game balances all it's weapons with strengths and disadvantages, too; While you can go [i]'pew pew'[/i] and kill stuff that way, some robots can deflect arrows.  While your hammer can certainly bonk those guys aside, now you're being shot full of holes by bow-wielding enemies.  While your sword can deflect that, it's range is too short and you are now at risk of receiving the [b]forever bonk[/b] from MC Hammerlots over there.  And while your spear has minced Hammerlots' head, his fifteen friends are now out for your oil.  So on, so forth.  Multiplayer is present and fun, too; Duels, a battle royale that's actually good, and co-operative play all round off an otherwise solid experience, and it's arguably the best part of CDiTDZ.

In terms of performance, this game runs smoothly, but be aware that voxels are anything but lightweight; This game can be a bit taxing on CPUs and GPUs alike in terms of temperature, so make sure your stuff's relatively flame-resistant before going in.  Otherwise, my CPU held a perfectly stable frame rate, save for multiplayer, where server lag becomes everybody's worst enemy, alongside the raptors that fires lasers from their faces.

While the game's story mode is relatively short, a surprisingly addicting Endless mode, several single and multiplayer challenges, and the multiplayer itself make Clone Drone rather replayable, and it supports Workshop levels in case you get tired of the game's stock levels and want to mix things up, from simply adding new arena layouts, to outright adventure maps that go beyond the arena's bounds to create long gauntlets of foes for you to die horribly to.

All told, it's a solid indie package that offers a fun time, and while it's no GoTY contender, Clone Drone is a deliciously delightful time that I can solidly recommend.  [u]Get it at MSRP, you won't be disappointed.[/u]

author: {'steamid': '76561198370149996', 'num_games_owned': 36, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 5510, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3099, 'last_played': 1685983597}
review:
This is a game that falls in the "Hard Fun" range of difficulty. My only complaint is the lack of weapons (as of writing this). I would like to see a few new upgrades.
1: Make the great-sword an upgrade instead of restricting it to multiplayer and the level editor.
2: Give the spear a shield re-enforcement upgrade (make it more durable), or give it a range upgrade (make it longer).
3: Give the hammer a faster swing speed or shorter cool-down.
4: Give the bow more arrow width, or more arrow speed.
5: Give the potential for 5 energy bars.
6: Give an even faster get-up upgrade.

For weapons I would like to see.
1: A grenade projectile that has the same effect as spider-tron's bombs. (Range and blast force for upgrades)
2: Dual-wield daggers (a faster but weaker version of sword) (only 2 ticks of projectile block and one tick of fire).
3: Scythe (fire and size upgrades)
4: An actual F***ing Gun (this would use up energy, because it would shoot small energy orbs, and would be deflected by projectile block) (Faster firing speed and less energy consumption for upgrades).
5: Claws like the zombies have (size and fire upgrades).
6: Energy Boomerang (size and fire for upgrades).

MEME weapons.
1: Frying pan (size upgrades).

Weapon re-skins
1: hammer: Stop sign (with an option for an "!" instead of "stop" in reference to "Madness Combat").
2: sword: Katana.
3: spear: Tribal Spear (shield would have a different design on it to).
4: bow: Mechanical Bow.
5: ALL: Choose what color you want the weapons/glow to be (from the already available options).

That is all from me.

author: {'steamid': '76561198894585267', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 4831, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3319, 'last_played': 1708720153}
review:
This game is a good game. The ability to play in gladiatorial combat without bloodshed makes this game a good choice for children. The multiplayer emotes are earned through actual effort instead of loot crates, and keep the game clean. (No profanity) The story mode has an interesting plot,[spoiler] and the fake human cracks me up every time! [/spoiler]. The achievements are full of diversity and some you may just get accidentally. There is a lot of workshop content existing of: 
Endless Levels
Adventure Levels
And Last bot Standing Levels
The presence of a fun and easy to use level editor always gives me joy, and the ability to toggle between only workshop levels, both workshop levels and regular endless levels, and only regular endless levels is a good feature of the game too. I do feel like the game needs the ability to make custom private duel maps as it is possible to make custom last-bot-standing maps so it would be possible, and it would complete the trifecta of endless, last-bot-standing, and private duels.
Altogether I feel like Clone Drone In the Danger Zone is a good game.

[b] Hikaye [/b]
[i] ƒ∞nsan v√ºcudu ba≈üka ya≈üam formlarƒ±na kar≈üƒ± √ßok dayanƒ±ksƒ±z olduƒüu i√ßin onlarƒ± bu ≈üekilde kullanmak pek yararlƒ± olmayacaktƒ±r . Robotlar ka√ßƒ±rdƒ±klarƒ± insanlarƒ±n zihinlerini bir robot v√ºcuduna aktarƒ±p onlarƒ± arenalarda g√º√ßl√º robotlarƒ±nƒ± test etmek i√ßin denek olarak kullanƒ±yordur . √áoƒüu insan her ne kadar robot v√ºcudunda olsa dahi en fazla 1 , 2 b√∂l√ºm sonra dayanamayƒ±p √∂l√ºyor dur . Biz ise bu arenaya d√º≈üen herhangi birini oynuyoruz √ß√ºnk√º her √∂ld√ºƒü√ºm√ºzde yerimize yeni bir insan ge√ßiyor ve onun g√∂z√ºnden oynamaya devam ediyoruz . Stage 10'a ge√ßtiƒüimiz vakit gizemli bir kadƒ±n hologramƒ± bizimle ileti≈üime ge√ßiyor ve az √∂nceki b√∂l√ºmden kalma robot kalƒ±ntƒ±larƒ±nƒ± toplayan "Garbage Bot"larƒ±n geleceƒüi yerin kapaƒüƒ±nƒ± bizim i√ßin acacaƒüƒ±nƒ± t√ºm insanlƒ±ƒüƒ±n kaderinin bizim ellerimizde olduƒüunu s√∂yl√ºyor . Delikten ge√ßtikten sonra Robotlar √ßƒ±ldƒ±rƒ±yor ve bizi durdurmaya √ßalƒ±≈üƒ±yor ancak √ßƒ±kƒ±≈ü kapƒ±sƒ±nƒ±n √∂n√ºnden ge√ßen bir arabaya atlayƒ±p oradan uzakla≈ütƒ±ƒüƒ±mƒ±zda bizi bulamayacaklarƒ± bir yere gidiyoruz . Tahmin edebileceƒüiniz √ºzere o kadƒ±n hologramƒ± az √∂nce anlattƒ±ƒüƒ±m kadƒ±nla aynƒ± ki≈üi . Adƒ±nƒ±n "Emilia" olduƒüunu belirten ablamƒ±z robotlarƒ±n liderleri olan y√ºce "Emperor" un d√ºnyaya yapacaƒüƒ± istilanƒ±n yakƒ±nda olduƒüunu s√∂yl√ºyor ve zaten yarƒ± insan yarƒ± robot olan zihnimizi d√ºnyaya saldƒ±rmasƒ± muhtemel olan bir geminin filosunda ki rastgele bir askere y√ºkleyeceƒüini o asker ile farkedilmeden gemiyi ele ge√ßirip istilayƒ± durdurmamƒ±zƒ± istiyor . [b] Oynanƒ±≈ü [/b]
[i] Evet oyunun asƒ±l olayƒ± olan oynanƒ±≈ü kƒ±smƒ±na geldik , en ba≈üta da s√∂ylediƒüim √ºzere bu oyun bir voxel-destruction oyunu . Kƒ±saca pixel par√ßalanma oyunu . [i] Standart d√º≈üman tipi olarak g√∂rebileceƒüimiz 5 Robot √ße≈üidi var ekstralarƒ± saymaz isek . Bunlar : Sword-Robot , Archer-Bot , Spider-Tron , Hammer-Bot ve Jetpack-Botlar dƒ±r . Oyuna en √ße≈üitlilik saƒülayan unsurlardan biri bu g√ºncelleme kƒ±smƒ± . Her oynanƒ±≈üƒ±nƒ±zda yeni bir build yapabilirsiniz . author: {'steamid': '76561198291023551', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 3415, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 182, 'playtime_at_review': 1379, 'last_played': 1711781079}
review: Clone Drone in the Danger Zone is a simple game, you simply fight robots and kill robots while trying not to die in the danger zone. From the outside your first look might be "this game looks really simple and the style reminds me of Minecraft with the "blockyness", but let me tell you there is so much more to this game than it seems. The story: The story was one of the things that got me and my brother hooked to this game, the story seems so simple and the next thing you know, your in a completely different feeling game. The physics: The physics are pretty good when it comes to aiming your weapon, you see your able to cut off different limbs depending on where your looking while your swing, and if you take damage you don't die right away (sometimes) instead you can still fight while only having... lets say half of your boy, one arm, 2 knees, half a head gone, its pretty astounding really. Online mode and Extras: once your done with the base game there are still a lot of things you can do like for example fight together or against other players. The game gives your challenges in order to unlock trophies, upgrades, or skins if your playing online. There's also an endless mode where you have to keep fighting and see how far you can go. This game seems so simple and it... kinda is, but if you can find the true beauty of this game, you will love it.
